ownedComment.body: The central element of this diagram is ComposedStructure. It holds n inner AssemblyContexts and n inner AssemblyConnectors.
Overview on AssemblyConnector and AssemblyContext. An AssemblyConnector is a bidirectional link of two assembly contexts.
DelegationConnectors connect inner and outer roles of a ComposedStructure. A ComposedStructure has n ProvidedDelegationConnectors and n RequiredDelegationConnectors.
A package holding all composable entities

ownedComment.body: An AssemblyConnector is a bidirectional link of two assembly contexts. Intuitively, an AssemblyConnector connects a provided and a required interface of two different components. AssemblyContext must refer to the tuple (Role, AssemblyContext) in order to uniquely identify which component roles communicate with each other.
